Google Announces Veo 2
----------------------

From TechCrunch ( https://techcrunch.com/2024/12/16/google-deepmind-unveils=
-a-new-video-model-to-rival-sora/ ) :

Google DeepMind, Google=E2=80=99s flagship AI research lab, wants to beat O=
penAI at the video-generation game =E2=80=94 and it might just, at least fo=
r a little while. On Monday, DeepMind announced Veo 2, a next-gen video-gen=
erating AI and the successor to Veo, which powers a growing number of produ=
cts across Google=E2=80=99s portfolio. Veo 2 can create two-minute-plus cli=
ps in resolutions up to 4k (4096 x 2160 pixels). Notably, that=E2=80=99s 4x=
 the resolution =E2=80=94 and over 6x the duration =E2=80=94 OpenAI=E2=80=
=99s Sora can achieve.

It=E2=80=99s a theoretical advantage for now, granted. In Google=E2=80=99s =
experimental video creation tool, VideoFX, where Veo 2 is now exclusively a=
vailable, videos are capped at 720p and eight seconds in length. (Sora can =
produce up to 1080p, 20-second-long clips.) VideoFX is behind a waitlist, b=
ut Google says it=E2=80=99s expanding the number of users who can access it=
 this week.

Eli Collins, VP of product at DeepMind, also told TechCrunch that Google wi=
ll make Veo 2 available via its Vertex AI developer platform =E2=80=9Cas th=
e model becomes ready for use at scale.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9COver the coming m=
onths, we=E2=80=99ll continue to iterate based on feedback from users,=E2=
=80=9D Collins said, =E2=80=9Cand [we=E2=80=99ll] look to integrate Veo 2=
=E2=80=99s updated capabilities into compelling use cases across the Google=
 ecosystem =E2=80=A6 [W]e expect to share more updates next year.=E2=80=9D

